Virtualization allows you to run given OS on HOST machine irrespective of what is HOST machine's OS
but you need to install entire guest OS on given host machine and using hypervisor host machine will provide resources to guest os
but with help of docker we will only install necessary libraries and binaries on given host machine to run guest OS and with the help
of docker engine(which contains docker daemon, API, cli and docker cli interacts with docker daemon with docker api, also that daemon lies in host os) it will
provide resources to that guest os
docker daemon is responsible for interacting with docker containers and images

